<br>
I think one point that gets overlooked frequently if the RP cover up for needed classes.<br>
<br>
A lot of guilds have invited those with an alignment that does not fit their guilds' simply to gain a class that is needed.  It is in an effort to avoid this type of thing that we choose not to RP the anyone can be evil thing.  <br>
<br>
Alignment has been a factor since D&amp;D and before.  It balances the game, promotes struggle and provides an established framework to compensate for the differences between people.  They are guidelines to allow for an enviroment that needs to remain consistent.  <br>
<br>
Inthul, I will miss you my friend.  You were one of the few that understood the evil only thing.    <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=464072"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/fatjohn/Warpriest.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flayedjaggedblade>Flayed Jaggedblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/6/03 3:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drama</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I have had people (Mostly Cielo ) refuse my rezzes, click off my buffs, curse me out, etc., for the sake of roleplay, but those are the moments I enjoy most in the game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
